## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of current research and the inherent complexity of human psychology. The findings are based on general trends and may not account for individual differences. Additionally, the rapidly changing nature of conspiracy theories, especially with the influence of social media, presents challenges in capturing the full scope of the phenomenon. Further research is needed to explore the long-term effects of conspiracy beliefs on individual and societal well-being.